## Addressing Potential Questions & Concerns



**Q: How do your agents ensure data privacy if they are autonomous?**



A: Our agents operate within a secure "harness" that separates execution from core model training [cite: 4]. They are programmed to perform tasks without persisting or "learning from" client data in a way that would expose it to other users or broader models [cite: 4]. Furthermore, our agents, Ezra and Jessa, operate under strict access control protocols initiated only after a signed NDA is in place [cite: 4].



**Q: Are your agents "black-box" systems?**



A: No. We utilize a **4-Step Verification Matrix** that ensures every autonomous proposal is logged, audited, and human-verified [cite: 4]. Our transparency protocol provides an audit trail for all significant decisions, ensuring stakeholders always understand the rationale behind an action [cite: 4].



**Q: How do you prevent "model drift" or loss of ethical alignment?**



A: We employ a recursive training loop that is continuously tempered by human oversight [cite: 4]. By involving the **Neighbor Oversight Committee**—which includes external researchers and ethicists—we ensure our agents are held to rigorous ethical standards that evolve with collaborative input rather than isolated automation [cite: 4].



**Q: Why partner with SovereignLab instead of other platforms?**



A: We are not merely providing software; we are offering an ecosystem of **Stewardship** [cite: 4]. Our model is built for institutions that require demonstrable accountability and want to lead in the development of ethical AI rather than just consuming it [cite: 4].



